Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Arrange garlic and vegetables in a 15 X 10 inch baking pan with sides. Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Roast 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, cook and drain pasta as directed on package. Place in large serving bowl. Mash roasted garlic with fork. Toss garlic and vegetables into the hot pasta.